==Demographics==
The population of Massieville was 584 at the 2020 census, of those 584 people, 91% were [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|White]], 2.5% were [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|African American]], 1.8% were [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|Hispanic or Latino]], 0.1% were [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|Asian]], 0.1% were from [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|other races]], and 5.9% were from two or more races. <ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Massieville_CDP,_Ohio?g=160XX00US3948230#race-and-ethnicity |access-date=2025-07-28 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

